The Limpopo Education is awaiting a report into a bullying incident at Mbilwi Secondary School in Thohoyandou. (Screenshot) POLOKWANE - The Limpopo school girl who allegedly assaulted learner Lufuno Mavhunga -- which may have led to her suicide -- has been arrested.
The 15-year-old has been charged with assault. READ: District officials probe Limpopo bullying incident The brutal incident was captured on video and went viral on social media earlier this week. In the clip, the suspect can be seen repeatedly slapping Lufuno. READ: Limpopo Education probes school bullying incident The victim was later found dead by her mother after an apparent overdose. An inquest docket into the teenager's death has been opened.